As shown in Table 1
                         listing the top 10 DElncRNAs from the microarray data, Gm39727 was the most up-regulated lncRNA and Gm36904 was the most down-regulated one, which were caused by 25 μg/mL N-GQDs treatment. Moreover, LOC102636183 and Gm41753 were the most up-regulated and down-regulated DElncRNAs caused by 100 μg/mL N-GQDs treatment, respectively (Table 2
                        ), while Gm40331 and 4930447J18Rik were the most up-regulated and down-regulated DelncRNAs caused by 100 μg/mL A-GQDs treatment, respectively (Table 3
                        ). When comparing the DElncRNAs caused by 100 μg/mL N-GQDs and 100 μg/mL A-GQDs treatments, the most up-regulated DElncRNA and down-regulated DElncRNAs were Gm15471 and Gm12408, respectively (Table 4
                        ). Meanwhile, all DElncRNAs of each group were self-segregated into clusters in heatmaps that were generated using hierarchical clustering analysis (Fig. 2
                        ).
